  "audio": "/audio/ஆ.mp3",
  "peculiarities": "ஆ is the long partner of அ: the same open sound held longer, like the 'a' in 'father'. When you stretch Ah! into Aah!, you are already saying it. Tamil pairs most of its vowels this way, a short sound and a long sound, and the ear learns to hear the difference.\n\nLook at the shape: ஆ begins just like அ, then adds a long open curl, as if our snake kept gliding for one extra beat.",
